@startuml fig-ssh-paramiko-workflow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Paramiko SSH Workflow — Remote Execution and SFTP Transfer

participant "ssh-client\n(Python + Paramiko)" as C #FFE0B2
participant "ssh-server\n(openssh-server)\nlabuser:labpass" as S #C8E6C9
database "Shared Volume\n/home/labuser/storage" as V #FFF9C4

== 1. SSH Connection ==

C -> S : SSH2 handshake\n(host key exchange)
S -[#43A047]-> C : authentication accepted\n(password: labpass)

== 2. Remote Command Execution ==

C -> S : exec_command("uname -a")
activate S
S -[#43A047]-> C : stdout: Linux ssh-server ...\n→ saved to ssh_output.txt
deactivate S

== 3. SFTP Upload ==

C -> S : open SFTP session
C -[#1565C0]> S : sftp.put("local_upload_file.txt",\n"/home/labuser/storage/uploaded_from_client.txt")
S -> V : write file
S -[#43A047]-> C : upload complete

== 4. SFTP Download ==

C -[#1565C0]> S : sftp.get("/etc/hostname",\n"downloaded_hostname.txt")
S -[#43A047]-> C : file content\n→ saved locally

C -> S : close SFTP + SSH

legend right
  Paramiko provides a Python API for SSH2:
  exec_command() runs remote shell commands,
  open_sftp() enables file transfers.
  Docker service names resolve via internal DNS.
endlegend
@enduml
